  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oropharyngeal dysphagia (OD) is a common morbidity after stroke that disrupts swallowing
      physiology. The investigators aimed at evaluating the prevalence of oropharyngeal dysphagia
      (OD) after stroke and analysing the risk factors and associated complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
